HEADWORD: Homaxonial
<hw>Hom`ax*o"ni*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Homo-</ets> + <ets>Gr</ets>. <ets><?/</ets> an axle,
axis.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Relating to that kind of homology
or symmetry, the mathematical conception of organic form, in which all
axes are equal. See under <er>Promorphology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

